    "dialogue": [
        {
            "text": "My name is Roderick, a knight in training for Altea. I will do my best to prove my use.",
            "context": "joined"
        },
        {
            "text": "This castle welcomes Heroes, but does that include me? I'm only a knight in training!",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "The leader we had in our platoon back home is someone I deeply respected. I have to admit that you remind me somewhat of that person!",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I want to become a true knight of Altea, and thus a man of any importance. But to do that, I must complete my time as a knight in training.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I have known my friend Luke for a long time. He may act rashly, but I know he has a good heart.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I would like to join you to scout the area outside of the castle. It's always best to be prepared for anything.",
            "context": "castle"
        },
        {
            "text": "I beg your pardon. I'm Roderick, a knight in training. I bring greetings from <Friend Name>.",
            "context": "friend"
        },
        {
            "text": "I'll savor this only for a moment. There's work to do.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "How encouraging. Slow and steady wins the race.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "I may falter at this rate. I must work harder.",
            "context": "level"
        },
        {
            "text": "I owe you thanks plus a vow to give you my all.",
            "context": "growth"
        },
        {
            "text": "Have I yet proven my use? I hope I have grown strong enough to be of great help to you. I find it hard to know whether I measure up, but I sense that I haven't disappointed you. I promise that I'll keep doing my best not to be a burden. I hope to even lighten your load. This order relies so much on your strength. I can't imagine what it must be like to bear that load. But if you'll allow me to remain...? I will help you carry it.",
            "context": "maxed"
        }
    ],
